  "doc_id": "3560",
  "text": "The above case also highlights the depth of knowledge and complexity of lies that may be involved in factitious disorder. However, the deceit is often more obvious. In one case, a 40-year-old woman presented to an orthopaedic department with a Google image of a dislocated ankle which she attempted to pass as her own radiograph. [CITATION_1] Factitious disorder was soon suspected based on various inconsistencies between the radiograph and the woman's own presentation.",
